Durban - The two men accused of killing businessman Avinash Manjanu made their second appearance in the Lenasia Magistrate’s Court last Wednesday. 
Gesen Perumal, 41, and Dinesh Moodley, 32, were charged with murder after they allegedly shot Manjanu, 31, pictured, during a birthday party at a councillor’s home last month. The case was adjourned to February. Manjanu, who was standing outside DA Councillor Vinay Choonie’s home, sustained five gunshot wounds and died at the scene. Read: 21st bash at councillor’s home ends in tragedy 
It is alleged he was trying to resolve a dispute between his brother, Bashan, and one of the suspects. POST